    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Filter</title>
        <figure id="f3350010270" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk13/K13009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil filter installation</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil System Module</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter (spin-on)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter gasket</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill oil filter with the proper grade and viscosity of engine oil. See Engine Operation and
                Maintenance Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate new oil filter gasket with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not overtighten oil filter.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spin oil filter on oil system module until filter gasket initially makes contact. Using an
                oil filter wrench with a band width of 38 mm (1.5 in) or greater, tighten filter an additional turn.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
